{"questionId":"9067174","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Mild heartburn is treated with antacids such as calcium carbonate.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the volume of CO<sub>2</sub> (g), in dm<sup>3</sup>, produced at STP, when 1.00 g of CaCO<sub>3</sub> (s) reacts completely with stomach acid.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>M<sub>r</sub></em> CaCO<sub>3</sub> = 100.09</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>n</em> CaCO<sub>3</sub> = «&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.00{\\text{ g}}}}{{100.09{\\text{ g mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.00</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100.09</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =» 0.00999 «mol»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">volume CO<sub>2</sub> = «0.00999 mol × 22.7 dm<sup>3</sup> mol<sup>–1</sup> = » 0.227 «dm<sup>3</sup>»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Accept 0.224 «dm<sup>3</sup>» if 22.4 dm<sup>3</sup> mol<sup>–1 </sup>is used as molar volume.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct answer.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067174","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ1.a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"